        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "docs: add direct Kubernetes manifest apply path",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fixes #91455.\n- Removes the Helm-focused wording from the Kubernetes install guide.\n- Adds `scripts/k8s/manifest.yaml` as a single-file manifest for direct `kubectl apply` workflows.\n- Keeps the existing `scripts/k8s/manifests/` and `deploy.sh` path unchanged.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm check:docs`\n- `OPENCLAW_CHECK_CHANGED_REMOTE_CHILD=1 OPENCLAW_CHANGED_LANES_RAW_SYNC=1 CI=1 PNPM_CONFIG_VERIFY_DEPS_BEFORE_RUN=false node scripts/check-changed.mjs --base upstream/main --head HEAD --timed -- docs/install/kubernetes.md scripts/k8s/manifest.yaml`\n- Verified `scripts/k8s/manifest.yaml` semantically matches `kubectl kustomize scripts/k8s/manifests`.\n- Verified in a temporary Kind cluster: Secret created, `scripts/k8s/manifest.yaml` applied, Deployment reached `1/1`, PVC bound, `/healthz` live, `/readyz` ready.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Kubernetes docs no longer frame Helm negatively and now provide a direct single-file manifest path for `kubectl apply`.\n\nReal environment tested: Local Kind Kubernetes cluster using Docker.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Created a temporary Kind cluster, created the `openclaw` namespace and `openclaw-secrets`, applied `scripts/k8s/manifest.yaml`, waited for rollout, then port-forwarded `svc/openclaw`.\n\nEvidence after fix: `deployment/openclaw` reached `1/1`, pod was `Running`, PVC was `Bound`, and the service answered health probes.\n\nObserved result after fix: `/healthz` returned `{\"ok\":true,\"status\":\"live\"}` and `/readyz` returned `{\"ready\":true,...}`.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live model-provider calls; the Kind smoke used a dummy provider key and only verified Kubernetes deployment, gateway startup, and health/readiness.\n",
